policykit-gnome: policykit-gnome (PolicyKit Framework for GNOME Integration)
policykit-gnome:
policykit-gnome: PolicyKit is an application-level toolkit for defining and handling 
policykit-gnome: the policy that allows unprivileged processes to speak to privileged 
policykit-gnome: processes. It is a framework for centralizing the decision making 
policykit-gnome: process with respect to granting access to privileged operations for 
policykit-gnome: unprivileged applications. PolicyKit is specifically targeting 
policykit-gnome: applications in rich desktop environments like Linux.
policykit-gnome:
policykit-gnome: This package contains PolicyKit extensions for the GNOME Desktop.
